        detailed_explanation "For an organization utilizing cloud services, it is crucial that the Cloud
            +b Service Provider (CSP) allows the extraction of both structured and
            +b unstructured data in a format that is widely recognized and used across the
            +b industry. This capability ensures data portability, which is essential for
            +b avoiding vendor lock-in, complying with data protection regulations, and
            +b maintaining operational continuity. Structured data refers to organized data,
            +b often stored in databases with defined fields; examples include data in .xls or
            +b .xml formats. Unstructured data, on the other hand, includes information that
